## JAVASCRIPT (Extension)

- Vanilla JS only — no build step, no bundler.
- Use `const` by default, `let` only when reassignment is necessary. Never `var`.
- Use `async/await` — no raw `.then()` chains.
- Wrap all `fetch` calls and `chrome.*` API calls in `try/catch`.
- No inline styles except the overlay positioning offset (dynamic value). All other styles go in injected `<style>` tags.
- Use `?.` optional chaining and `??` nullish coalescing instead of manual null checks.
- DOM manipulation: prefer `element.innerHTML` for template rendering, `createElement` for single nodes.
- No external libraries — keep extension self-contained.

---

## PROJECT STRUCTURE RULES

- One file = one responsibility. No god files.
- `routers/` — HTTP interface only. Call services, return responses.
- `services/` — Business logic. No FastAPI imports.
- `models/` — Pydantic schemas and type aliases. No logic.
- Tests mirror source structure: `tests/services/test_detector.py` mirrors `app/services/detector.py`.

