## WHAT CURSOR MUST NEVER DO

- Never use `Any` in type hints without a `# noqa: ANN401` and a comment.
- Never suppress mypy errors with `type: ignore` without explaining why in the same line.
- Never put business logic inside a FastAPI route handler.
- Never use `time.sleep()` in async code — use `await asyncio.sleep()`.
- Never call `client.messages.create(...)` synchronously inside an `async def` — use the async client.
- Never send `document.body.innerHTML` to the backend — visible text only.
- Never let an AI failure propagate as an HTTP 500 — catch and fall back to rule-based messages.
